explanations.content:
Từ giả thiết ta thay $x$ bởi $\dfrac{x-1}{2}$, ta có
$f\left(x\right)+f\left(2-x\right)=\dfrac{x^2-2x+1}{x^2-2x+5}$
	Lại có
	\begin{eqnarray*}
	& &\int_{-1}^{1}f\left(x\right)dx=\int_{-1}^{3}f\left(2-x\right)dx\\
	&\Leftrightarrow&2I=\int_{-1}^{3}\dfrac{x^2-2x+1}{x^2-2x+5}dx=\int_{-1}^{3}dx-4\int_{-1}^{3}\dfrac{dx}{\left(x-1\right)^2+4}
	\end{eqnarray*}
	Đặt $x-1=2\tan t$.$\\$
	$\Rightarrow \displaystyle\int\limits_{-1}^{3} \dfrac{1}{\left(x-1\right)^2+4} \mathrm{\,d}x=\dfrac{1}{2}\displaystyle\int\limits_{-\frac{\pi}{4}}^{\frac{\pi}{4}} dt \mathrm{\,d}t=\dfrac{\pi}{4}$$\\$
	$\Rightarrow 2I=4-\pi\Leftrightarrow I=2-\dfrac{\pi}{2}$.

Với điều kiện đã cho, ta có 
		\begin{eqnarray*}
			& & f'(x)\sqrt{x^2+1}=2x\sqrt{f(x)+1} \Rightarrow \displaystyle\int\dfrac{f'(x)\mathrm{d}x}{\sqrt{f(x)+1}}=\displaystyle\int\dfrac{2x\mathrm{d}x}{\sqrt{x^2+1}}\\
			&\Rightarrow& \displaystyle\int\dfrac{\mathrm{d}(f(x)+1)}{\sqrt{f(x)+1}}=\displaystyle\int\dfrac{\mathrm{d}(x^2+1)}{\sqrt{x^2+1}} \Rightarrow \sqrt{f(x)+1}=\sqrt{x^2+1} +C.
		\end{eqnarray*}
		Vì $f(0)=0$ nên $C=0$. Từ đó ta có $\sqrt{f(\sqrt{3})+1}=\sqrt{(\sqrt{3})^2+1} +0 \Rightarrow f(\sqrt{3})=3$.

$f(x)\cdot f(a-x)=1\Rightarrow f(x)=\dfrac{1}{f(a-x)}$.
        \begin{eqnarray*}
        I=\displaystyle\int\limits_0^a \dfrac{\mathrm{\,d}x}{1+f(x)} &=& \displaystyle\int\limits_0^a \dfrac{\mathrm{\,d}x}{1+\dfrac{1}{f(a-x)}}
         =\displaystyle\int\limits_0^a \dfrac{f(a-x)}{1+f(a-x)}\mathrm{\,d}x\\
         &=& -\displaystyle\int\limits_0^a \dfrac{f(a-x)}{1+f(a-x)}\mathrm{\,d}(a-x)= -\displaystyle\int\limits_a^0 \dfrac{f(t)}{1+f(t)}\mathrm{\,d}t\\
         &=& \displaystyle\int\limits_0^a \dfrac{f(t)}{1+f(t)}\mathrm{\,d}t=\displaystyle\int\limits_0^a\dfrac{f(x)}{1+f(x)}\mathrm{\,d}x.
        \end{eqnarray*}
        $2I=\displaystyle\int\limits_0^a \dfrac{\mathrm{\,d}x}{1+f(x)}+\displaystyle\int\limits_0^a\dfrac{f(x)}{1+f(x)}\mathrm{\,d}x=\displaystyle\int\limits_0^a\mathrm{\,d}x=a$. Vậy $I=\dfrac{a}{2}$.

Gọi $I$ là tích phân đã cho. Ta có
\begin{align*}
\left[\ln(\cos x+2\sin x)\right]'=\ &\dfrac{-\sin x+2\cos x}{\cos x+2\sin x}=\dfrac{(-\sin x+2\cos x)(\cos x+2\sin x)}{(\cos x+2\sin x)^2}\\
=\ & \dfrac{2\cos 2x+3\sin x\cos x}{\cos^2x+4\sin^2x+4\sin x\cos x}\\
=\ & \dfrac{4\cos2x+3\sin 2x}{4\sin 2x-3\cos2x+5}.
\end{align*}
Đặt $\begin{cases} u=\ln(\cos x+2\sin x)\\ \mathrm{d}v=(4\cos 2x+3\sin 2x)\mathrm{\,d}x\end{cases}\Rightarrow \begin{cases} \mathrm{d}u=\dfrac{4\cos2x+3\sin 2x}{4\sin 2x-3\cos2x+5}\mathrm{\,d}x\\ v=\dfrac{1}{2}\cdot\left(4\sin2x-3\cos 2x+5\right)\end{cases}$.$\\$
Suy ra
\begin{align*}
I=\ &\dfrac{1}{2}(4\sin2x-3\cos2x+5)\cdot\ln(\cos x+2\sin x)\Bigg|_{0}^{\tfrac{\pi}{2}}-\dfrac{1}{2} \displaystyle\int\limits_{0}^{\tfrac{\pi}{2}}(4\cos2x+3\sin2x)\mathrm{\,d}x\\
=\ & 4\ln2-\dfrac{1}{2}\left(2\sin2x-\dfrac{3}{2}\cos2x\right)\Bigg|_{0}^{\tfrac{\pi}{2}}=4\ln2-\dfrac{1}{2}\left(\dfrac{3}{2}+\dfrac{3}{2}\right)=4\ln2-\dfrac{3}{2}.
\end{align*}
Vậy $c=4,\ a=3,\ b=2$. Suy ra $T=a+b+c=9$.

Đặt $I=\displaystyle\int\limits_0^1\left[f'(x)\right]^2\mathrm{\,d}x=\displaystyle\int\limits_0^1(x+1)e^xf(x)\mathrm{\,d}x=\dfrac{e^2-1}{4}$. $\\$ Xét
		\begin{align*}
		\displaystyle\int\limits_0^1e^xf(x)\mathrm{\,d}x=\left.xe^xf(x)\right|_0^1-\int\limits_0^1x\mathrm{\,d}\left(e^xf(x)\right)=-\int\limits_0^1\left(xe^xf(x)+xe^xf'(x)\right)\mathrm{\,d}x.
		\end{align*}
		Suy ra
		$$\displaystyle\int\limits_0^1 x e^x f'(x)\mathrm{\,d}x= -\int\limits_0^1xe^xf(x)\mathrm{\,d}x-\int\limits_0^1e^xf(x)\mathrm{\,d}x=-I=\dfrac{1-e^2}{4}.$$
		Khi đó
		\begin{align*}
		\displaystyle\int\limits_0^1f'(x)\left(f'(x)+xe^x\right)\mathrm{\,d}x=\int\limits_0^1\left(\left[f'(x)\right]^2+xe^xf'(x)\right)\mathrm{\,d}x=\int\limits_0^1\left[f'(x)\right]^2\mathrm{\,d}x+\int\limits_0^1xe^xf'(x)\mathrm{\,d}x=0.
		\end{align*}
		Do $f(x)$ có đạo hàm liên tục trên $[0;1]$, $xe^x$ liên tục trên $[0;1]\subset \mathbb{R}$, $\displaystyle\int\limits_0^1\left[f'(x)\right]^2\mathrm{\,d}x\neq 0$, suy ra $f'(x)\neq 0$ với mọi $x\in [0;1]$ nên $$f'(x)=-xe^x\Rightarrow f(x)=-\displaystyle\int xe^x=-\displaystyle\int x\mathrm{\,d}e^x=-xe^x+\int e^x\mathrm{\,d}x=-xe^x+e^x+C.$$
		Từ $f(1)=0$ suy ra $C=0$. Vậy $f(x)=-xe^x+e^x.$ Do đó
		\begin{align*}
		\displaystyle\int\limits_0^1f(x)\mathrm{\,d}x=\int\limits_0^1\left(-xe^x+e^x\right)\mathrm{\,d}x=-\int\limits_0^1xe^x\mathrm{\,d}x+\int\limits_0^1e^x\mathrm{\,d}x&=-\int\limits_0^1x\mathrm{\,d}e^x+\int\limits_0^1e^x\mathrm{\,d}x\\
		&=-xe^x\Big|_0^1+2\int\limits_0^1e^x\mathrm{\,d}x=-e+2e^x\Big|_0^1\\
		&=-e+2(e-1)=e-2.
		\end{align*}

Đặt $t=1-x$, thì $x\in[0;1]\Leftrightarrow t\in[0;1]$.$\\$
Ta có
\begin{eqnarray*}
&& f(x)+2f(1-x)=3x^2-6x\Leftrightarrow f(x)+2f(1-x)=3(x-1)^2-3\\
&\Leftrightarrow & f(1-t)+2f(t)=3t^2-3\Leftrightarrow 2f(x)+f(1-x)=3x^2-3.
\end{eqnarray*}
Xét hệ phương trình
\begin{eqnarray*}
&& \begin{cases} f(x)+2f(1-x)=3x^2-6x\\ 2f(x)+f(1-x)=3x^2-3\end{cases}\Leftrightarrow \begin{cases} f(x)+2f(1-x)=3x^2-6x\\ 4f(x)+2f(1-x)=6x^2-6\end{cases}\\
& \Rightarrow & 3f(x)=3x^2+6x-6\Leftrightarrow f(x)=(x+1)^2-3, \forall x\in[0;1].
\end{eqnarray*}
Khi đó $f(1-x^2)=(2-x^2)^2-3=x^4-4x^2+1$.$\\$
Suy ra $I=\displaystyle\int\limits_0^1 f\left(1-x^2\right)\mathrm{\, d}x=\displaystyle\int\limits_0^1\left(x^4-4x^2+1\right)\mathrm{\, d}x=-\dfrac{2}{15}$.
